0.081 0 (Overview)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1061 M
0.029 0 (Separate compilation of templates has been part of C++ since before the ARM was published.  In its)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1111 M
0.087 0 (November 1994 meeting, the committee reaffirmed separate compilation; that reaffirmation appeared in)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1161 M
0.022 0 (the May 1995 CD.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1236 M
0.119 0 (John Spicer submitted a proposal in the pre-Santa Cruz mailing to remove separate compilation for)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1286 M
0.116 0 (templates.  At the Santa Cruz meeting, he resubmitted that proposal, which was changed only by the)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1336 M
0.039 0 (addition of a list of \223sponsors.\224  That proposal raises several objections to separate compilation, which the)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1386 M
0.097 0 (Core3 working group discussed at length on March 11 and the committee discussed in a technical session)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1436 M
0.128 0 (during the evening of March 11.  Based on the discussions in that working group meeting and elsewhere,)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1486 M
-0.008 0 (I believe that the objections do not hold up.  The reasons follow.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F4_50
Ji
296 1611 M
0.177 0 (Clarity of description)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1683 M
0.154 0 (The strongest claim is that separate compilation has so many problems in its description that it is not clear)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1733 M
0.061 0 (whether they can be resolved in time to produce a good standard.  Further examination, however, showed)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1783 M
0.032 0 (that almost all of the problems remain even in the absence of separate compilation, because they show up)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1833 M
0.078 0 (when combining templates and namespaces.  Thus removing separate compilation does not significantly)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1883 M
-0.048 0 (reduce the committee\222s workload.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F4_50
Ji
296 2008 M
0.170 0 (Ease of implementation)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2080 M
0.015 0 (Spicer\222s proposal claims that the new model has never been implemented.  However, two working group)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2130 M
0.003 0 (members said they have implemented it.  At least one of those implementations is likely to become)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2180 M
0.084 0 (commercially available.  In subsequent discussion, John Spicer said that he thought separate compilation)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2230 M
0.002 0 (was implementable.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F4_50
Ji
296 2355 M
0.180 0 (Efficiency)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2427 M
0.028 0 (The proposal also claims that separate compilation \223cannot be implemented efficiently enough to be)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2477 M
0.075 0 (usable.\224  That is surely a matter of opinion, and one about which users should be allowed to make their)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2527 M
0.002 0 (own tradeoffs.  Separate compilation is intrinsically more efficient for large systems because it requires)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2577 M
0.102 0 (only template declarations to be reprocessed for each translation unit and not their definitions also.)A
